article.headline: Vermont 88, Dartmouth 71
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- Marqus Blakely, Mike Trimboli and Garvey Young combined for 69 points to lead Vermont to a 88-71 victory over Dartmouth on Tuesday night. Vermont (4-2) shot 65 percent from the field in the first half to take a 42-34 lead into the break and wound up hitting 59 percent for the night. Dartmouth pulled within 55-52 with 12:05 remaining, but the Catamounts went on a 15-2 run over the next five minutes to take a 70-54 lead. Blakely led Vermont with 27 points and 11 rebounds, while Trimboli scored 23 and Young scored a career-high 19 points as the Catamounts recorded their third straight victory. Alex Barnett led Dartmouth (1-5) with 32 points, including 6-of-7 3-pointers.
